article.headline: Houston 85, Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 65
article.story: HOUSTON -- Aubrey Coleman scored 22 points and had 10 rebounds to help lead Houston to an 85-65 victory over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi on Tuesday night. Marcus Cousin also had a double-double for the Cougars (9-3) with 14 points and 10 rebounds off the bench. Kelvin Lewis added 20 points. Qa'rraan Calhoun scored 13. Lewis scored eight points in an 11-2 run early in the first half to give Houston the lead for good. Houston led 43-29 at the half. Kevin Palmer led the Islanders (6-9) with 17 points. Justin Reynolds added 13. Demond Watt had nine points and 10 rebounds.
